    • produceOutputByConsumingInputsOneAfterAnother

      protected void produceOutputByConsumingInputsOneAfterAnother(IntermediateResultElementSink sink) throws ExecOpExecutionException, ConsumingPushBasedPlanThreadException
      Consumes the complete i-th input first (and pushes that input to the operator op), before moving on to the (i+1)-th input. Hence, this implementation does not consume the inputs in parallel. Instead, if one of the inputs requires a long time, no progress is made in parallel based on any of the other inputs.
      Throws:
      ExecOpExecutionException
      ConsumingPushBasedPlanThreadException

    • produceOutputByConsumingAllInputsInParallel

      Consumes the complete i-th input first (and pushes that input to the operator op), before moving on to the (i+1)-th input.
      Throws:
      ExecOpExecutionException
      ConsumingPushBasedPlanThreadException

    • advanceIndexOfInput

      protected int advanceIndexOfInput(int currentIndex)
      Returns the given integer increased by one, unless such an increase results in an integer that is outside of the bounds of the inputs array, in which case the function returns zero (effectively jumping back to the first index in the array).
